transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, Jelena speaking.

Speaker 2: Is this Jelena?

Speaker 1: Yes, it is, sir. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Well, I've been trying to get a hold of people for over 30 minutes.

Speaker 1: This is David Walls. I seem to have a problem.

Speaker 2: They're not sending me nothing. I don't know what's going on.

Speaker 1: I can't even get in my email. I log in my deal and it says not valid.

Speaker 2: Interesting. Okay, Mr. Walls, I have your account pulled up here.

Speaker 1: The good news is the doctor has already concluded the medical portion.

Speaker 2: So it looks like the prescription was written and it's currently at the pharmacy.

Speaker 1: And then the pharmacy should probably ship it out to you today.

Speaker 2: Well, supposedly he said I needed to quit taking beetroot.

Speaker 1: I do see a note of that. It says reach out to patient on beetroot concern waiting for a response again.

Speaker 2: I can't get a hold of nobody. I don't know.

Speaker 1: It takes forever to get a hold of anybody to talk to them.

Speaker 2: Okay, so let me read what the doctor said.

Speaker 1: It said, hello, the pharmacy would like to confirm that you will discontinue taking beetroot before starting Viagra.

Speaker 2: As the combination can cause potential interactions and cause a serious decrease in blood pressure.

Speaker 1: The pharmacy cannot ship the order until it is confirmed.

Speaker 2: And then there's another note sent to you yesterday.

Speaker 1: It says, hello, the pharmacy would like to confirm that you will discontinue taking beetroot.

Speaker 2: And then, yeah, just the same thing as before.

Speaker 1: They cannot because of the interaction with the Viagra.

Speaker 2: So do you agree to stop taking the beetroot?

Speaker 1: Do I? Yes, I will. I mean, I'd like to try that. I was hoping to be here by Thursday.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's the only thing that's been to hold up is they wanted a response from you,

Speaker 1: but I can reply on your behalf and let the doctor know that you've agreed to stop taking the beetroot

Speaker 2: while you're taking the Viagra.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I just don't take the beetroot when I take the Viagra or stop it completely?

Speaker 2: I would say stop it completely.

Speaker 1: Well, I mean, the other Viagra, there's no problem with it.

Speaker 2: The one I get from my doctor, but this, you got something different?

Speaker 1: I don't know why they're saying that there could be a combination, but it has to do with your blood pressure.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay, all right, well, then I'll quit. I mean, I've been paid for it. I need to get it, you know.

Speaker 1: And I'd like to try it, but I mean, I was supposed to try it on Thursday, but that ain't going to work.

Speaker 2: So, okay, so they'll ship it out today?

Speaker 1: Yes, I'm replying on your behalf that you're going to stop taking the beetroot,

Speaker 2: and I'm going to message the following week that they'll release that hold and ship it out to you.

Speaker 1: Okay, but it'll be shipped today?

Speaker 2: Yes, it will.

Speaker 1: And it takes three to five days?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: So, best scenario would be Friday?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm going to ask them to expedite it and ship it out to you today.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So, hopefully you'll get it by Friday.

Speaker 1: My God, how come it's so hard to get a hold of you guys?

Speaker 2: I know, especially in the mornings. We've just been so busy because the AGD has been in such high demand.

Speaker 1: And I do apologize. I had a customer on the line before you.

Speaker 2: I saw that you were in the queue on my extension, and I just could not get off the phone with him.

Speaker 1: So, I do apologize for that, but I've gone ahead and taken care of that for you, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, all right. Thank you.

Speaker 1: You're awesome.

Speaker 2: Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa. Let me ask you another question.

Speaker 1: I've tried to log in. I've tried to log in, and it wouldn't let me log in.

Speaker 2: Is there – I have – it's casinodavidcox.net.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: If I want to log in to –

Speaker 1: casinodavidatcox.net, yep.

Speaker 2: Not David, just Casino Dave.

Speaker 1: Oh, nope. I have Casino David. Let me change it to Casino Dave.

Speaker 2: Yes, let's go to Casino Dave, because that's where the problem's been.

Speaker 1: Yeah, casinodavidatcox.net.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And now I should be able to log in?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: If I have to or whatever.

Speaker 2: Yeah, casinodavidatcox.net.

Speaker 1: And I just sent you a link to be able to log in.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, we're good, then. I'm going to get it shipped out today.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir. You are.

Speaker 2: Okay. Well, I didn't take it today, so I guess I'm good, huh?

Speaker 1: Yeah, you are.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Thank you all.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Pleasure.

Speaker 1: Thank you. All right. Bye.
